<TITLE> Private TV owners to propose policy </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 12 (bdnews24.com)  The government asked television channel owners to submit recommendations within three days on formulation of a policy for setting up and operating private TV stations, a government official said Sunday. After a meeting with TV station owners Sunday, the information ministry's additional secretary Mamunur Rashid Chowdhury told reporters that TV owners were also asked to submit recommendations on amendment of the present policy. TV owners and their representatives at the meeting urged the government not to issue any new licenses without analysing the ad market. They also asked the government to allow them to expand and run sister channels under the same license. Ekushey TV chairman Abdus Salam said the country's advertising market was very small compared to the number of TV stations. "The government should not issue any more licenses now," Salam said. He also said the government's liberal attitude to awarding TV licenses to the private sector might affect the media with political influence. b
